<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id62859495-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa" identifier="/us/usc/t25/s1934"><num value="1934">§ 1934.</num><heading> “Indian” defined for certain purposes</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">For the purposes of sections 1932 and 1933 of this title, the term “Indian” shall include persons defined in section 1603(c) <ref class="footnoteRef" idref="fn002116">1</ref><note type="footnote" id="fn002116"><num>1</num> See References in Text note below.</note> of this title.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id62859496-4962-11f1-add1-b56d3fa293fa">(<ref href="/us/pl/95/608/tII/s204">Pub. L. 95–608, title II, § 204</ref>, <date date="1978-11-08">Nov. 8, 1978</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/92/3077">92 Stat. 3077</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
